<subSubSection id="C32F65354E0EFFC8978800A4FABA4214" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E0EFFC8978800A4FD4346D8" blockId="41.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E0EFFC8978800A4FE824668" bold="true" box="[151,273,762,787]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennomere III as long as pedicel, flabellum 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8943900A5FCC34668" box="[806,848,763,787]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">
3– 
<date id="FF8B107E4E0EFFC8945D00A5FCC34668" box="[834,848,763,787]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">4</date>
</number>
x longer than antennomere III. Maxillary palpomere IV 
<date id="FF8B107E4E0EFFC897DE0141FF4E464C" box="[193,221,799,823]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC897DE0141FF5C464C" box="[193,207,799,823]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="4.0">4</number>
x
</date>
longer than III. Pronotum with lateral margins divergent posteriad, anterior margin notably projected. Abdominal sternum VIII with posterior margin straight. Pygidium with median lobe acuminate, slightly longer than lateral lobe, as wide as 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC896FE0139FE784604" box="[481,491,871,895]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC896EA0139FD964604" box="[501,517,871,895]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="2.0">2</number>
posterior margin width; indentations between lateral lobe and median lobe well developed; lateral lobe well developed, acuminate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E0EFFC897D801F0FCA14174" blockId="41.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E0EFFC897D801F0FECB46BC" bold="true" box="[199,344,942,967]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Colouration</emphasis>
: (
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E0EFFC8966F01F0FE5146BC" box="[368,450,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 18" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,202,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[155,1431,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 18. Habitus. 10 Amydetes caetite sp. nov.. 11 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov.. 12 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov.. 13 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 14 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 15 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov.. 16 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 17 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov.. 18 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252105/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC896BA01F1FE5146BC" box="[421,450,943,967]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) Integument yellowish-brown. Prothorax generally with two maculae yellowish-brown on the sides, expansions pale yellow. Elytron with distal 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8943A018DFCBC4690" box="[805,815,979,1003]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC89426018DFCDA4690" box="[825,841,979,1003]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="2.0">2</number>
or apices black, often with suture and outer margin pale yellow. Abdomen with up to posterior 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8956201A9FD144174" box="[637,647,1015,1039]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8958D01A9FD324174" box="[658,673,1015,1039]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="2.0">2</number>
dark-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E0EFFC897D80644FCF541E5" blockId="41.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E0EFFC897D80644FE944148" bold="true" box="[199,263,1050,1075]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Head</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E0EFFC896020644FEE94148" box="[285,378,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 40" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1758,1781]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,204,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1737]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 40. Frons shape drawings 23 Amydetes agnita. 24 A. apicalis. 25 A. discissa. 26 A. fastigiata. 27 A. fucata. 28 A. lucioloides. 29 Amydetes solaris sp. nov.. 30 Amydetes goiana sp. nov.. 31 Amydetes manezinha sp. nov.. 32 Amydetes caetite sp. nov.. 33 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov.. 34 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov.. 35 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 36 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 37 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov.. 38 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 39 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov.. 40 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 250 µm. DBA = distance between antennifers antennifers. DBAS = distance between antennal sockets." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252107/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
Figs. 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC896430645FEE94148" box="[348,378,1051,1075]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="40.59">40</number>
</figureCitation>
, 59) Fronto-clypeus depressed up to antennal sockets, anterior margin 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC893890644FB334148" box="[1174,1184,1050,1075]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC893B40644FB294148" box="[1195,1210,1050,1075]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="5.0">5</number>
wider than distance between antennal sockets and slightly wider than distance between antennifers. Antenna with 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC893D30661FA81412C" box="[1228,1298,1087,1111]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="30.5" valueMax="32.0" valueMin="29.0">29–32</number>
antenomers (n= 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC897DD063DFF434100" box="[194,208,1123,1147]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="3.0">3</number>
); antennomere III as long as pedicel, flabellum 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC895FE063DFC984100" box="[737,779,1123,1147]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">
3– 
<date id="FF8B107E4E0EFFC895E2063DFC984100" box="[765,779,1123,1147]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">4</date>
</number>
x longer than antennomere III. Labrum rounded. Maxillary palpomere IV 
<date id="FF8B107E4E0EFFC8962606D9FEC741E4" box="[313,340,1159,1183]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8962606D9FED441E4" box="[313,327,1159,1183]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="4.0">4</number>
x
</date>
longer than III, as long as labial palpomere III.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E0EFFC897D806F4FC944028" blockId="41.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E0EFFC897D806F4FEB341B8" bold="true" box="[199,288,1194,1219]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Thorax</emphasis>
. (Figs. 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8966706F5FE5341B8" box="[376,448,1194,1219]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="78.96">78, 96</number>
) Pronotum with lateral margins divergent posteriad, anterior margin notably projected, posterior angles well developed, acute and deflexed. Setigerous punctures irregularly separeted 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC892010690FAB4419C" box="[1310,1319,1230,1255]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
–1.5x the diameter of a puncture. Hypomeron slightly less than 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8941006ADFC8A4070" box="[783,793,1267,1291]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8943C06ADFCA04070" box="[803,819,1267,1291]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="4.0">4</number>
longer than high. Elytron slightly dehiscent, slightly wider subapically; marginal costa with anterior margin not projected. Scutellum with lateral margins convergent posteriad. Mesosternum with posterior margin rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E0EFFC897D80700FC8C4278" blockId="41.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E0EFFC897D80700FEAF400C" bold="true" box="[199,316,1374,1399]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Abdomen</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E0EFFC896470700FE59400C" box="[344,458,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 116 – 124" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[237,1354,182,1541]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[231,1355,181,1545]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 116 – 124. Abdomen, ventral. Note the lanterns and posterior margin of abdominal sternite V and VIII. 116 Amydetes caetite sp. nov .. 117 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov .. 118 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov.. 119 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 120 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 121 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov .. 122 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 123 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov. 124 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252114/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Figs. 124</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E0EFFC896C30701FD9B400C" box="[476,520,1375,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 134 – 142" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1548,1571]" captionTargetBox="[257,1322,209,1521]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[247,1339,193,1527]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 134 – 142. Pygidium, dorsal. 134 Amydetes caetite sp. nov.. 135 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov.. 136 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov. 6. 137 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 138 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 139 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov.. 140 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 141 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov.. 11. 142 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 500 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252116/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">142</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E0EFFC895040700FDED400C" box="[539,638,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 208 – 219" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1781,1804]" captionTargetBox="[287,1297,545,1742]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[280,1307,519,1757]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 208 – 219. Teminalia. FIGURES 208, 212 and 216 syntergite (dorsal) and abdominal sternite (ventral). FIGURES 209 – 211, 213 – 215, 217 – 219 Aedeagus, dorsal (209, 213, 217), ventral (210, 214, 218), lateral (211, 215, 219). FIGURES 208 – 211 Amydetes marajoara sp. no v .. 212 – 215 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov .. 216 – 219 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252124/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
216– 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8954B0700FDED400C" box="[596,638,1374,1399]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="219.0">219</number>
</figureCitation>
) Abdominal sternum V with posterior margin straight. Abdominal sternum VI with lantern as long as 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8953907DDFDA140E0" box="[550,562,1411,1435]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8952307DDFDD940E0" box="[572,586,1411,1435]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="4.0">4</number>
sternum length and as wide as 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC894AF07DDFC2940E0" box="[944,954,1411,1435]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC894DB07DDFC4740E0" box="[964,980,1411,1435]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="2.0">2</number>
sternum width. Abdominal sternum VII with lantern as long as 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC896AD07F9FE2D40C4" box="[434,446,1447,1471]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC896D807F9FE4640C4" box="[455,469,1447,1471]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="4.0">4</number>
sternum length and as wide as 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8944907F8FCF040C4" box="[854,867,1446,1471]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8947207F8FCE940C4" box="[877,890,1446,1471]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="5.0">5</number>
sternum width. Abdominal sternum VIII with posterior margin straight or irregular. Pygidium with median lobe acuminate, slightly longer than lateral lobe, as wide as 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC897EB07B1FF6D437C" box="[244,254,1519,1543]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8961707B1FE84437C" box="[264,279,1519,1543]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="2.0">2</number>
posterior margin width; indentation between lateral lobe and median lobe well developed; lateral lobe well developed, acuminate. 
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E0EFFC896CF044CFDCE4350" bold="true" box="[464,605,1554,1579]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Terminalia:</emphasis>
Syntergite with anterior margin truncate and posterior asymmetric, lateral margins slightly convergent posteriad, with um a pair of wisp of bristles laterally. suture between abdominal tergites IX and X indistinct. Abdominal sternum IX slightly more than 
<date id="FF8B107E4E0EFFC894B10405FC594308" box="[942,970,1627,1651]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC894B10405FC2F4308" box="[942,956,1627,1651]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
longer than syntergite, slightly more than 
<date id="FF8B107E4E0EFFC897880421FF2043EC" box="[151,179,1663,1687]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC897880421FF3643EC" box="[151,165,1663,1687]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
longer than wide; wider at posterior 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8957B0421FDFC43EC" box="[612,623,1663,1687]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC895650421FD1A43EC" box="[634,649,1663,1687]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="3.0">3</number>
; with lateral margins strongly divergent posteriad up to 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8920B0421FAB143EC" box="[1300,1314,1663,1687]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC892330421FAAB43EC" box="[1324,1336,1663,1687]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="3.0">3</number>
sternum length, bristled at posterior 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC896D404FDFE4543C0" box="[459,470,1699,1723]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC896FD04FDFE6243C0" box="[482,497,1699,1723]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="3.0">3</number>
; posterior margin irregular. 
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E0EFFC8943504FCFC3443C0" bold="true" box="[810,935,1698,1723]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Phallobase asymmetric. Parameres close-set subapically, rounded apically. Phallum 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC895430499FDF443A4" box="[604,615,1735,1759]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E0EFFC8956E0499FDEC43A4" box="[625,639,1735,1759]" pageId="41" pageNumber="242" value="3.0">3</number>
longer than paramere, apex rounded, subparallel-sided, ventral plate well-sclerotized and straight, apical expansions indistinct.
</paragraph>
